    affiliation: "Department of Agronomy, Purdue University"
repository-code: "https://github.com/<your-username>/WheatFlagLeaf"
abstract: >-
  A physics-informed machine learning framework for winter wheat phenology.
  The physical core (WES) adapts Wang & Engel (1998)'s three-phase DVS-rate
  model with Streck et al. (2003)'s generalised vernalization function f(V).
  WES outputs are coupled with HLS satellite phenometrics in a five-model ML
  ensemble (ElasticNet, Ridge, Random Forest, XGBoost, LightGBM). Predicts
  eight winter wheat phenological stages (emergence to maturity) at 30 m
  field scale across the US Plains using HLS Landsat-Sentinel and Daymet
  daily weather.
keywords:
  - winter wheat
  - phenology
  - remote sensing
  - vernalization
  - Wang-Engel
  - Streck
  - machine learning
  - HLS
